
/*
 * This Hyperlambda HTTP API endpoint retrieves and returns the originating IP address of the HTTP request.
 *
 * 1. [.arguments]
 *    * Declares an empty argument block, meaning the endpoint does not require any input parameters from the caller.

 * 2. [request.ip]
 *    * Fetches the IP address of the client making the request.
 *    * This is typically the public IP address visible to the server.

 * 3. [yield]
 *    * Returns the value from [request.ip] to the caller under a node named [ip].
 */
.arguments

// Retrieving IP address from equest.
request.ip

// Returning IP address to caller.
yield
   ip:x:@request.ip
